{{Quote|The captain of the ''Flanchard'' was Pter Nyklas, and he was about as bad as it got - a believer in High Human Culture who saw the bridge of an Impstar as a license to kill. Worse for the Empire, the ''Flanchard'' frequently handled slaving details, a duty most Imperial captains loathed but Nyklas seemed to love.|[[Voren Na'al/Legends|Voren Na'al]]|<ref name="TEGtW" />}}
'''Pter Nyklas''' was a [[Human/Legends|Human]] [[Gender/Legends|male]] [[Officer/Legends|officer]] who served in the [[Imperial Navy/Legends|Imperial Navy]].

==Biography==
In [[5 BBY/Legends|5 BBY]], Nyklas was overseeing a construction project on the [[Imperial Hall of Heroes]]. He was also responsible for the purchase of the [[Wookiee/Legends|Wookiee]] [[Slavery/Legends|slaves]] used to build the new wing.

[[File:Han_saves_Chewbacca.jpg|thumb|left|200px|Solo stuns Nyklas to save Chewbacca.]]

During an exchange with the [[Trandoshan/Legends|Trandoshan]] slavers that supplied the slaves, Nyklas discovered that [[Ssoh]]'s starship had been disabled. Nyklas ordered his [[TIE/ln space superiority starfighter/Legends|TIE/LN starfighters]] under the command of [[Lieutenant/Legends|Lieutenant]] [[Han Solo/Legends|Han Solo]] to [[Skirmish near Komnor|destroy]] the ship, but Solo belayed the strike order when he discovered the Wookiees onboard. Nyklas ordered Solo and his pilots to kill the survivors, but instead Solo delivered the leader of the revolt, a Wookiee named [[Chewbacca/Legends|Chewbacca]]. Infuriated, Nyklas ostensibly removed Solo's flying privileges.

Returning to [[Coruscant/Legends|Coruscant]], Nyklas whipped Chewbacca regularly, regardless of his performance. When Chewbacca rose up in anger against Nyklas, the Imperial commander drew his blaster and was only stopped from shooting the Wookiee by Solo. As the pair fled, Nyklas filed Solo's dishonorable discharge papers and swore revenge on them. Nyklas's cruelty was a pivotal factor in driving Solo from the Imperial Navy, forging Chewbacca's [[Life debt/Legends|life debt]] to the young Imperial officer, and eventually leading to Solo and Chewbacca's service with the Rebel Alliance - for which, one officer of [[New Republic Intelligence]] noted wryly, the whole galaxy owed Nyklas a great debt of gratitude.

==Personality and traits==
Nyklas was described as being the stereotypical cruel Imperial. He was a believer in [[High Human Culture/Legends|Human High Culture]] and saw the bridge of an [[Imperial-class Star Destroyer/Legends|Imperial Star Destroyer]] as a license to kill. His ship, the ''[[Flanchard]]'', frequently handled slaving runs, a duty that Nyklas loved even though most other ship captains loathed it.

